trend_summary: Land use remained overwhelmingly rural. Initial images show patchy forest clearance for farms; mid-period frames display modest forest recovery, then the latest scene exhibits widespread clear-cutting and bare soil in the northern uplands. Agricultural parcels consolidate and expand slightly, with minor road-side settlement growth, keeping built-up cover sparse overall.
notable_changes: Large-scale clear-cutting/bare soil spreads across the northwest and central ridges in the latest image.
Cropland blocks enlarge and merge, replacing smaller patchwork fields in the east and south.
Minor extension of road corridors and scattered rural dwellings, but no significant urban nodes emerge.
